{
  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The densities of three steels were calculated as 6.92, 6.88 and 6.78 g/cm^3 for 0.5C, 0.8C and 1.2C steels respectively.",
    "The stacking fault energy (SFE) values of austenite in 0.5C and 0.8C steels are 73.4 and 77.9 mJ/m^2 and that of 1.2C steel is 84.5 mJ/m^2.",
    "Specific strength of 0.8C steel is 142.3 MPa cm^3/g.",
    "Table 1 chemical compositions (mass %): 0.5C: Al 9.90, Mn 17.71, C 0.48; 0.8C: Al 9.91, Mn 17.14, C 0.77; 1.2C: Al 10.19, Mn 17.45, C 1.16; all balanced with Fe."
  ],
